Bugatti has completed production of the 99th and final W16 Mistral, bringing the legendary 8.0-litre quad-turbocharged W16 era to a close after two decades of redefining the hypercar world. Named “The Last of Its Kind,” the final roadster is finished in an elegant two-tone Pearl and Sparkle exterior with a bespoke Magnolia leather interior, serving as a fitting tribute to an engine that powered icons like the Veyron, Chiron, and Mistral.
The W16 Mistral also leaves behind an extraordinary legacy as the world’s fastest open-top production car, having reached 453.91 km/h (282 mph). As Bugatti enters the Tourbillon era with its naturally aspirated V16 hybrid powertrain, the final Mistral marks the closing chapter of one of the most celebrated engines ever built.
